==English==

===Adjective===
'''[[once]] [[removed]]''', also, less commonly, '''[[once-removed]]''' (''no'' {{compar}} ''or'' {{superl}} ''forms'')

# (''family relationship'') One [[generation]] apart.
#:''Phil and Andre are first cousins '''once removed'''.''

====Usage notes====
If two cousins are from different [[generation]]s to the common ancestor, the term ''[[removed]]'' indicates how many generations apart they are.

For example, if Phil and Marie are [[first cousin]]s (have a common grandparent), and Marie has a son Andre, Phil and Andre are first cousins once removed.

